    "translation": "Moses asked his Lord to show him the most knowledgeable of earth's people. Allah guided him to a servant from among His servants to whom We had given mercy and taught knowledge from Our presence. Moses said: May I follow you on condition that you teach me from what you have been taught of right guidance? He said: Indeed, you will not be able to have patience with me. And how can you have patience for what you do not encompass in knowledge? He stipulated that he not ask him about anything until he makes mention of it to him. So they set out, and he damaged the ship, killed the boy, and erected the wall. Moses did not have patience and asked about each action. The righteous servant informed him of the profound wisdom behind each action. Moses learned that behind appearances are hidden wisdoms known only to Allah. This is a story that teaches us submission to Allah's decree and that divine knowledge is vaster than human comprehension.",
