    "translation": "A righteous man had two sons. He raised them upon faith and good character. He gave them great counsel when he was dying. He said: O my sons, adhere to God-consciousness in private and public. And fulfill trust even to those who betray you. And maintain family ties even if they sever you. And be good to neighbors even if they wrong you. And be patient with affliction for it will pass. And be grateful in ease for it does not last. And learn beneficial knowledge and teach it to people. And earn lawful provision and spend from it in the way of Allah. Do not be deceived by the world for it is transient. And work for the Hereafter for it is lasting. They obeyed their father and acted upon his counsel. They became among the righteous reformers. Allah blessed their offspring until the Day of Judgment.",
